WEBVTT

00:00:00.850 --> 00:00:09.009
Welcome to JW Broadcasting. What's in store for us this month? If you've ever

00:00:09.009 --> 00:00:13.810
struggled with feelings of inadequacy, you'll relate to the experiences of

00:00:13.810 --> 00:00:19.850
Francis, Diego and Carla. They'll tell us how they came to appreciate their

00:00:19.850 --> 00:00:26.449
valuable place in Jehovah's congregation. When tragedy strikes, it's easy to

00:00:26.449 --> 00:00:31.210
feel overwhelmed. We'll learn how a brother who struggled to care for his family

00:00:31.210 --> 00:00:38.649
spirituality got the help he needed to regain his balance and his joy. And in our

00:00:38.649 --> 00:00:43.170
new music video, we'll see how learning the truth brings true comfort to those

00:00:43.170 --> 00:00:51.250
who draw close to Jehovah and his people. This is JW Broadcasting for May 2023.

00:00:51.250 --> 00:01:15.680
As Jehovah's servants, nothing brings us greater joy than worshiping the true

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:23.400
God. But we are also human. This means that from time to time, any of us can

00:01:23.400 --> 00:01:29.959
and probably will experience unsettling moments. Times when we question our

00:01:29.959 --> 00:01:36.519
worth. For example, have you ever wondered about your true value in Jehovah's

00:01:36.599 --> 00:01:42.959
eyes? Have you ever experienced moments of anxiety about your place in his

00:01:42.959 --> 00:01:50.719
organization? Or have you struggled with feelings of worthlessness? Such thoughts

00:01:50.719 --> 00:01:56.439
can erode our joy. And we might even begin to doubt our personal worth to

00:01:56.439 --> 00:02:03.959
Jehovah. If that has happened to you, you're not alone. Centuries ago, the

00:02:03.959 --> 00:02:10.879
writer of Psalm 94 revealed that he too was overwhelmed by anxieties. Let's

00:02:10.879 --> 00:02:20.210
read it together at Psalm 94 and verse 19. The writer is addressing Jehovah. When

00:02:20.210 --> 00:02:25.889
anxieties overwhelmed me, you comforted and soothed me. Now notice the footnote

00:02:25.889 --> 00:02:34.370
on verse 19, disquieting thoughts. These can arise from factors such as guilt

00:02:34.409 --> 00:02:41.129
over the fact that we cannot do more in the ministry or in the congregation. Fear

00:02:41.129 --> 00:02:46.849
of the future of being separated from the ones we know and love and despair

00:02:46.849 --> 00:02:52.129
from being overlooked, feeling that we don't really matter. Disquieting

00:02:52.129 --> 00:02:58.530
thoughts are real and can overwhelm us at times. They can rob us of our inner

00:02:58.530 --> 00:03:04.449
peace and our sleep. And if we're not careful, they can even stifle our prayers,

00:03:04.449 --> 00:03:12.129
damaging our relationship with Jehovah. Nothing would make Satan happier. We never

00:03:12.129 --> 00:03:18.449
want that to happen, especially now, since this old world is so near to closing.

00:03:18.449 --> 00:03:25.050
So what can help us to soothe these disquieting thoughts? In this month's

00:03:25.050 --> 00:03:31.169
broadcast, we will find the answer in a heartwarming prophecy. We hope that

00:03:31.169 --> 00:03:37.090
this inspired message will provide a strong scriptural basis to help you to

00:03:37.090 --> 00:03:43.449
dispel any feelings of inadequacy. Which prophecy? Well, please open your Bible

00:03:43.449 --> 00:03:49.689
to Isaiah chapter 56. Here we read of one of the most touching expressions of

00:03:49.729 --> 00:03:55.490
Jehovah's appreciation for two groups of people. Both groups wanted to serve

00:03:55.490 --> 00:04:01.490
Jehovah, but under the Mosaic law, they were limited or even disqualified from

00:04:01.490 --> 00:04:07.330
fully participating in Jehovah's arrangement for pure worship. Who were they?

00:04:07.330 --> 00:04:16.649
Let's read Isaiah chapter 56, verse 3. The foreigner who joins himself to

00:04:16.649 --> 00:04:22.930
Jehovah should not say, Jehovah will surely separate me from his people. And the

00:04:22.930 --> 00:04:30.089
eunuch should not say, Look, I'm a dried up tree. Did you notice the two groups,

00:04:30.089 --> 00:04:36.889
foreigners or non-Israelites and eunuchs, men who physically could not produce

00:04:36.889 --> 00:04:43.889
children? They faced very difficult and possibly disheartening circumstances.

00:04:43.889 --> 00:04:49.009
During Isaiah's time, uncircumcised foreigners were allowed to live in

00:04:49.009 --> 00:04:54.569
Israel, but they had no permanent ties with the nation. Because of their

00:04:54.569 --> 00:05:00.329
status, they could not eat of the Passover meal. And as a protection, the

00:05:00.329 --> 00:05:06.449
Israelites were not to associate closely with them. But many foreigners came to

00:05:06.449 --> 00:05:12.170
love Jehovah, converted to pure worship, and served Jehovah alongside his

00:05:12.170 --> 00:05:20.009
people. They were called proselytes. Nevertheless, even they could not fully

00:05:20.009 --> 00:05:25.930
become part of the nation of Israel. How would you feel if you were a foreigner

00:05:25.930 --> 00:05:32.449
alive at that time? Your biggest fear would be getting cut off from God's people.

00:05:32.449 --> 00:05:39.370
Might you have disquieting thoughts at times? Consider the second group. Isaiah

00:05:39.370 --> 00:05:46.170
mentioned eunuchs. These were men who had their reproductive organs removed. It

00:05:46.170 --> 00:05:51.329
was the custom of Eastern pagan nations to make eunuchs out of some of the male

00:05:51.329 --> 00:05:56.050
children, taken captive in war, and then assigned them to serve as trusted

00:05:56.050 --> 00:06:02.610
officials in royal courts or in other settings. It appears that during the days of

00:06:02.610 --> 00:06:08.490
Isaiah, some of these Gentile eunuchs learned about Jehovah, came to love him and

00:06:08.490 --> 00:06:15.319
decided to align themselves with Jehovah's people. These eunuchs enjoyed a

00:06:15.319 --> 00:06:19.519
measure of acceptance among Jehovah's people, and they had the privilege of

00:06:19.519 --> 00:06:25.560
worshipping Jehovah. However, because they were eunuchs, they could not become

00:06:25.560 --> 00:06:32.720
fully-fledged members of the congregation of Israel. Plus, at that time and in

00:06:32.720 --> 00:06:37.720
that culture, they suffered great humiliation and not being able to father

00:06:37.720 --> 00:06:44.920
children. Do you think they experienced disquieting thoughts at times? We know

00:06:44.920 --> 00:06:52.480
they did. But Isaiah reveals something significant about this group. Jehovah loved

00:06:52.480 --> 00:07:00.160
them. In effect, Jehovah says to them, I know how you feel. Now let me tell you

00:07:00.160 --> 00:07:11.500
how I feel about you. Let's read Isaiah chapter 56, verses 4 and 5. For this is

00:07:11.500 --> 00:07:16.100
what Jehovah says to the eunuchs, who keep my sabbaths and who choose what I

00:07:16.100 --> 00:07:22.339
delight in and who hold fast to my covenant. I will give to them in my house and

00:07:22.339 --> 00:07:28.420
within my walls a monument and a name, something better than sons and daughters.

00:07:28.420 --> 00:07:35.699
In everlasting name, I will give them one that will not perish. I will give them

00:07:35.699 --> 00:07:42.139
something better than sons and daughters. In everlasting name, their physical

00:07:42.139 --> 00:07:48.779
limitations did not diminish their value in the eyes of our loving God because of

00:07:48.779 --> 00:07:55.019
their whole soul obedience to Him. Jehovah would always remember them. They would

00:07:55.019 --> 00:08:01.620
have an everlasting name, one that would not perish. Jehovah treasured these

00:08:01.620 --> 00:08:06.420
faithful ones so much that he kept the memory of their service in his house

00:08:06.420 --> 00:08:14.740
within his walls like a monument so as to cherish them daily. Imagine how those

00:08:14.740 --> 00:08:20.459
eunuchs felt now knowing that their God had something special reserved for them.

00:08:20.620 --> 00:08:25.100
They knew Jehovah had heard their prayers. They knew that their God felt

00:08:25.100 --> 00:08:31.779
compassion for them. All those desquieting thoughts started to melt away. Those

00:08:31.779 --> 00:08:37.860
comforting words started to heal their broken spirit. But why did Jehovah make

00:08:37.860 --> 00:08:45.340
these promises to these two groups? What did he see that others may not have? We

00:08:45.379 --> 00:08:51.220
don't have all the details, but we do have some. They are revealed to us much

00:08:51.220 --> 00:08:58.419
later in time. And they give us valuable clues. For example, in the book of

00:08:58.419 --> 00:09:04.419
Nehemiah, we are introduced to two foreigners who are living among God's people.

00:09:04.419 --> 00:09:11.340
There's a significant detail about their names. Nehemiah chapter 3 and verse

00:09:11.340 --> 00:09:19.700
7 tells us they were Melataya, the Ghibinite, and Jaden, the Moranithite, who were

00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:27.059
of foreign descent. Yet their names tell a different story. What do they mean?

00:09:27.059 --> 00:09:36.460
Melataya means Jaha has provided escape. Jaden means Jehovah has given ear. How

00:09:36.500 --> 00:09:42.419
did they get those names? These men were likely born in Babylon, children of

00:09:42.419 --> 00:09:48.220
foreigners who joined in true worship in Israel and who were later taken captive

00:09:48.220 --> 00:09:56.940
in 607 BCE. The parents of these men were not natural Israelites. However, the

00:09:56.940 --> 00:10:02.179
names they chose for their children reflected their devotion and love for

00:10:02.179 --> 00:10:09.019
Jaha'uva's name. And the fact that these sons of non-Israelites would want to

00:10:09.019 --> 00:10:16.620
share and rebuilding Jerusalem shows how they themselves love Jaha'uva. How did

00:10:16.620 --> 00:10:22.940
Jaha'uva feel about these foreigners? Notice his prophetic words as we continue

00:10:22.940 --> 00:10:31.629
on at Isaiah chapter 56 verse 6 and 7. As for the foreigners who join themselves to

00:10:31.629 --> 00:10:36.669
Jaha'uva, to minister to him, to love the name of Jaha'uva and to be his

00:10:36.669 --> 00:10:42.389
servants, all those who keep the Sabbath and do not profane it and who hold fast

00:10:42.389 --> 00:10:47.950
to my covenant. I will also bring them to my holy mountain and make them rejoice

00:10:47.950 --> 00:10:53.549
inside my house of prayer. Their whole burnt offerings and their sacrifices will

00:10:53.549 --> 00:10:59.070
be accepted on my altar from my house will be called a house of prayer for all

00:10:59.070 --> 00:11:05.190
the peoples. Jaha'uva noticed that these foreigners faithfully observed the

00:11:05.190 --> 00:11:10.590
laws of a covenant that they could never be fully a part of. In verses 6 and

00:11:10.590 --> 00:11:17.429
7, Jaha'uva was in effect inviting them into his home, a house of prayer for

00:11:17.429 --> 00:11:23.710
all the peoples, Jew and foreigner alike. Hearing these words must have lifted

00:11:23.710 --> 00:11:28.509
their heavy hearts, but Jaha'uva did more than just tell them how much he

00:11:28.509 --> 00:11:35.710
valued them, he showed them. How? Among the foreigners who returned to the

00:11:35.710 --> 00:11:41.789
ruins of Jerusalem in 537 BCE were particular group of foreigners who had

00:11:41.789 --> 00:11:48.149
become proselytes, and they included descendants of the Ghiblianites, a nation

00:11:48.149 --> 00:11:53.389
that had joined themselves to Israel and served as gathers of wood and draws of

00:11:53.389 --> 00:11:59.429
water for the assembly and for Jaha'uva's altar. These descendants of the

00:11:59.429 --> 00:12:04.669
Ghiblianites had spent decades as captives in Babylon for crimes they did not

00:12:04.669 --> 00:12:11.230
commit. They had no land inheritance back in Israel. They were servants. Yet

00:12:11.230 --> 00:12:15.629
they traveled back to Israel and helped rebuild the temple and the walls of

00:12:15.629 --> 00:12:23.230
Jerusalem. What motivated them? They loved Jaha'uva. These descendants of

00:12:23.230 --> 00:12:28.870
Ghiblian expected nothing in return for their service, but they did receive

00:12:28.870 --> 00:12:34.309
something quite unexpected. After the Israelites received their portion land,

00:12:34.309 --> 00:12:40.110
this group called the Nethanem, who did not have a land inheritance, were

00:12:40.110 --> 00:12:45.750
assigned a place to live. Where would they be placed? Outside the city, in a

00:12:45.750 --> 00:12:52.389
slum, in some abandoned part of forgotten Jerusalem? No, the Bible tells us they

00:12:52.389 --> 00:12:58.190
were assigned to live in Ophol. Now take a look at the map and see for yourself

00:12:58.190 --> 00:13:05.389
where Ophol is located right next to the temple. Jaha'uva made these humble

00:13:05.389 --> 00:13:10.549
gathers of wood his neighbors. This underscores how much Jaha'uva loved and

00:13:10.549 --> 00:13:15.909
cherished these faithful foreigners who motivated by love that all they could

00:13:15.909 --> 00:13:22.509
to share in his worship. What's the lesson? Both the Unix and the foreigners

00:13:22.509 --> 00:13:27.990
were limited and what they could do in God's service. From a human standpoint,

00:13:27.990 --> 00:13:34.750
they were probably considered less than ordinary. Nothing special. Perhaps some

00:13:34.750 --> 00:13:41.950
even considered them outcasts. That is not how Jaha'uva viewed them. He knew each

00:13:41.950 --> 00:13:48.190
one by name. He listened to their prayers, and he viewed each individual as a

00:13:48.190 --> 00:13:55.629
precious gem. Where man sees the ordinary, our Heavenly Father sees the extra

00:13:55.629 --> 00:14:03.269
ordinary. To illustrate, what do you see here? If you are thinking sand, you are

00:14:03.269 --> 00:14:09.429
right. Sand is one of the most common substances on the earth. To us, it

00:14:09.429 --> 00:14:16.149
typically looks bland in an ordinary. Each particle identical to the next. No

00:14:16.149 --> 00:14:21.590
color, no sparkle, you never see someone show off a sand necklace or bracelet.

00:14:21.590 --> 00:14:29.629
But what happens if you look at sand under the microscope? To the naked eye, all

00:14:29.629 --> 00:14:36.309
sand looks the same and is pretty dull. But magnified a hundredfold or more, each

00:14:36.309 --> 00:14:42.070
individual grain of sand reveals distinct beauty. We see parts of shells and

00:14:42.070 --> 00:14:47.990
crystals, all contrasting in shapes and colors. There is a treasure trove and

00:14:47.990 --> 00:14:56.629
a handful of sand. That is how Jaha'uva sees each of you. Just as he saw the

00:14:56.629 --> 00:15:02.870
faithful foreigners in Unix, for the precious gems that they were, he sees you too.

00:15:03.590 --> 00:15:10.789
Yes, you who may be restricted by age, health, physical stamina, emotions, or

00:15:10.789 --> 00:15:15.590
family responsibilities from doing as much in some spiritual activities as you

00:15:15.590 --> 00:15:23.549
would like to. But those limitations do not define you. Remember that in God's

00:15:23.549 --> 00:15:29.750
eyes, your worth as a person is not measured by how much you do, but rather

00:15:30.149 --> 00:15:38.309
how much you try. With eternity and perfection in view, Jaha'uva chooses to see not your

00:15:38.309 --> 00:15:46.309
limitations, but your potential. When you serve Jaha'uva, wholesome, despite limited

00:15:46.309 --> 00:15:53.909
circumstances, you sparkle in his eyes. And because you shine so brightly in Jaha'uva's heart,

00:15:54.629 --> 00:15:58.230
he will always help you. He will always cherish you.

00:15:59.509 --> 00:16:03.590
Do you remember the faithful Psalmist who wrote about being overwhelmed by

00:16:03.590 --> 00:16:11.350
disquiring thoughts at Psalm 94 and 19? In the very next line, he tells Jaha'uva,

00:16:11.350 --> 00:16:19.110
you comforted and soothed me. By the way, who wrote that song? We don't know his name,

00:16:19.830 --> 00:16:26.629
but Jaha'uva does, and he carefully preserved that unknown writer's words for thousands of

00:16:26.629 --> 00:16:34.309
years in the Bible. Like the Psalmist, the Farner, the Unig, no matter the circumstances,

00:16:34.309 --> 00:16:40.309
when you humbly served Jaha'uva, when you try your best, your work is never frueless.

00:16:41.110 --> 00:16:47.830
In everlasting name is reserved for each of you, because your Heavenly Father cherishes you.

